window.SORTING_SCRIPT={BUBBLE:{START:()=>`Welcome to the Bubble Sort party! We're going to compare adjacent numbers and swap them if they're in the wrong order. The big numbers will bubble up to the top!`,COMPARING:(e,t)=>`Comparing ${e} and ${t}. Should they swap places?`,SWAPPING:(e,t)=>`Yes! ${e} is bigger than ${t}, so let's swap them. Bubble, bubble, toil and trouble!`,FIXED:e=>`Aha! The number ${e} has bubbled all the way to its final spot. It's locked in!`,SUCCESS:()=>`The party is over, and everyone is standing in line perfectly! All sorted.`},INSERTION:{START:()=>`Let's try Insertion Sort! It's like organizing a hand of cards. we'll take one number at a time and slide it into its perfect spot in the sorted section.`,PICKING:e=>`Picking up ${e}. Now let's find where it belongs in our sorted line.`,SLIDING:(e,t)=>`${e} is smaller than ${t}, so let's slide ${t} to the right to make some room!`,INSERTING:e=>`Found it! This is the perfect home for ${e}. Plop!`,SUCCESS:()=>`All cardsâ€”I mean numbersâ€”are organized! That's a winning hand.`},SELECTION:{START:()=>`Time for a scavenger hunt! Selection Sort will scan the messy part of the list to find the absolute smallest number and bring it to the front.`,SCANNING:e=>`Checking ${e}... is it the smallest one we've seen so far?`,NEW_MIN:e=>`Found a new winner! ${e} is currently the smallest. Let's keep looking.`,SWAPPING:(e,t)=>`Search complete! We're swapping our smallest find, ${e}, with ${t} at the front of the line.`,SUCCESS:()=>`The scavenger hunt is over. We've built a perfectly ordered line from smallest to largest!`},QUICK:{START:()=>`Ready for some speed? Quick Sort uses a pivot to divide the work! We'll put small numbers on the left and big ones on the right.`,PIVOT:e=>`Choosing ${e} as our Pivot! It's the judge for this round.`,PARTITIONING:(e,t)=>`Is ${e} smaller than our pivot ${t}? Let's move it to the correct side.`,RECURSING:e=>`Now let's repeat the magic on the ${e} group!`,SUCCESS:()=>`Divide and conquer was a success! The entire array is now lightning-fast sorted.`},HEAP:{START:()=>`Welcome to the Heap Sort construction site! First, we'll organize these numbers into a Max-Heap tree where every parent is larger than its children.`,HEAPIFY:(e,t)=>`Comparing parent ${e} with child ${t}. The parent must be the boss!`,EXTRACTING:e=>`The king of the heap, ${e}, is moving to his final spot at the end.`,REBUILDING:()=>`The king is gone! Let's reshuffle the tree to find the next largest leader.`,SUCCESS:()=>`The tree has been fully harvested! All numbers are sorted and ready to go.`},RADIX:{START:()=>`Radix Sort is all about looking at the digits! We'll sort everything by the ones place, then the tens, then the hundreds.`,BUCKETING:(e,t,n)=>`Looking at the ${n}s place of ${e}. It's a ${t}, so into bucket ${t} it goes!`,COLLECTING:e=>`Buckets full! Let's collect them back into the array, now sorted by their ${e}s place.`,SUCCESS:()=>`We've checked every digit! The numbers have been sorted through the power of place-values.`},COUNTING:{START:()=>`Welcome to Counting Sort! Instead of comparing numbers, we'll just count how many times each one appears. It's like taking a census!`,COUNTING:e=>`Spotted a ${e}! Let's increment our count for ${e}.`,CUMULATIVE:(e,t)=>`Calculating the position: everything up to ${e} needs ${t} spots in our final array.`,PLACING:(e,t)=>`Placing ${e} into its correct spot at index ${t}. No guessing needed!`,SUCCESS:()=>`The census is complete! Every number knows its place, and the array is perfectly sorted.`},BUCKET:{START:()=>`Time for Bucket Sort! We'll distribute these numbers into different buckets based on their range, then sort each bucket individually.`,BUCKETING:(e,t)=>`${e} belongs in the range for bucket ${t}. Off it goes!`,SORTING_BUCKET:e=>`Now let's sort the contents of bucket ${e} so they're in perfect order.`,COLLECTING:e=>`Bucket ${e} is ready! Let's pour its sorted contents back into our main array.`,SUCCESS:()=>`All buckets have been emptied and combined! Our scattered numbers are now one harmonious sorted list.`},COMB:{START:()=>`Let's try Comb Sort! It improves on Bubble Sort by using a gap to eliminate "turtles"â€”small values near the end of the list.`,GAP:e=>`Setting our comparison gap to ${e}. We'll compare elements that are this far apart.`,COMPARING:(e,t)=>`Comparing ${e} and ${t} with our current gap. Do they need a swap?`,SUCCESS:()=>`The gap has shrunk to one and all swaps are done! The turtles have been defeated and the array is sorted.`},CYCLE:{START:()=>`Welcome to Cycle Sort! This is an in-place, unstable sorting algorithm that is theoretically optimal in terms of the total number of writes.`,PICK_ITEM:e=>`Picking up ${e}. We're going to find its absolute correct position in the entire array.`,FIND_POS:(e,t)=>`Counting elements smaller than ${e}... it belongs at index ${t}.`,SWAPPING:(e,t)=>`Placing ${e} into its new home and picking up ${t} to continue the cycle.`,SUCCESS:()=>`Every item has completed its cycle and landed in its final destination. Minimal writes, maximum efficiency!`},SHELL:{START:()=>`Shell Sort is here! It's a generalized version of Insertion Sort that allows for the exchange of items that are far apart.`,GAP:e=>`Starting a new pass with a gap of ${e}. This helps move distant elements closer to their final spots.`,INSERTION:(e,t)=>`Performing a gap-based insertion for ${e} using our ${t}-step interval.`,SUCCESS:()=>`The gaps have closed and the final insertion pass is complete! The array is now fully organized.`}};